# Resume Flock — Project Context

Use this for continuity when starting a new session. Full session history and architecture notes live in **CLAUDE.local.md** at the project root.

## Recent behavior (current codebase)

- **Scene is STATIC** — Once created and positioned, scene elements are never repositioned. The bulls-eye is the 2D projection of the scene's X=0 onto the scene view plane; the focal point is a 2D element. Together they control the perspective projection (parallax transform) of 3D scene elements to the 2D plane; only that transform is updated, not element positions.

- **Focal point modes** — LOCKED/FOLLOWING: smaller display = circles and lines (SVG). DRAGGING: smaller display hidden; larger display = actual cursor file (crosshair). Element position always drives scene/parallax.

- **Motion parallax** runs only when (1) the scene is ready (`#scene-container`, `#scene-plane`, and at least one `.biz-card-div` or `.skill-card-div`), and (2) focal point or layout changes. Triggers: `focal-point-changed`, `bulls-eye-moved`, `scene-width-changed`, `resize`. No document/scene mousemove listeners. Effective focal position is read from the `#focal-point` DOM element. See `modules/composables/useParallaxVue3Enhanced.mjs`.

- **rDiv remove (×)**  
  All rDivs (originals and resume-list clones) are deleteable. Originals get the close handler in `ResumeItemsController.createBizResumeDiv`. Clones get it re-attached in `ResumeListScrollContainer._attachRDivCloseHandler` (because `cloneNode(true)` does not copy event listeners). Remove persists via `ResumeListController.removedJobNumbers`; `ensureJobInListing` / `scrollToElementId` re-add when needed.

- **Resume list**  
  Single list: job rDivs + appended skill card copies. Scroll by DOM id: `scrollToElementId('resume-' + jobNumber)`. List position/length shown in debug row. High-contrast text uses local `modules/utils/resumeFlockPaletteColors.mjs` (LAB L* threshold) and `paletteHelpers.mjs`.

- **color-palette-utils-ts** — Vendored **read-only**; **update from source** with **`npm run sync:color-palette-utils-ts`** (`package.json`). App loads palettes **only from S3** (configured in `.env`); **no fallbacks** — missing URL, fetch error, bad NDJSON, or invalid hex → fast-fail (`useColorPalette.mjs`). Color math: **`resumeFlockPaletteColors.mjs`**. See `color-palette-utils-ts/README-ts.md`.

